primvars:crypto_asset is ignored on instanceable references

An asset authors a constant primvars:crypto_asset on a parent Xform, inherited by
the descendant geometry and resolved as the Cryptomatte asset id. When the asset is
added through an instanceable reference, the inherited primvar reached the shape as a
single-element per-element (uniform) primvar and was declared as a size-1 uniform
array, which Arnold could not index per face ("out-of-range error (index N of 1)"),
leaving the crypto_asset AOV empty. Single-element uniform/varying/indexed primvars are
now declared as constant user data so the value applies to the whole shape.

Cryptomatte asset ids are name hashes that differ between the reading paths, so this test
asserts on the render log (no out-of-range / failed-lookup errors) rather than on pixels.

Fixes #2699

author: cyril.pichard@autodesk.com

